quran[32]{c,v,t,f}:
  74,55,"Then whoever wills will remember it."
  74,56,"And they will not remember except that Allāh wills. He is worthy of fear and adequate for [granting] forgiveness."
  77,43,"[Being told], "
  77,44,"Indeed, We thus reward the doers of good."
  77,45,"Woe, that Day, to the deniers."
  78,40,"Indeed, We have warned you of an impending punishment on the Day when a man will observe what his hands have put forth{1} and the disbeliever will say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., the deeds he did in this world, which await him in the Hereafter.]
  79,34,"But when there comes the greatest Overwhelming Calamity{1} -",footnotes:1:[i.e., the Day of Resurrection.]
  79,35,"The Day when man will remember that for which he strove,"
  79,36,"And Hellfire will be exposed for [all] those who see -"
  80,31,"And fruit and grass -"
  80,32,"[As] enjoyment [i.e., provision] for you and your grazing livestock."
  80,33,"But when there comes the Deafening Blast{1}",footnotes:1:[The piercing blast of the Horn which signals resurrection. Aṣ-Ṣākhkhah is also a name for the Day of Resurrection.]
  81,28,"For whoever wills among you to take a right course."
  81,29,"And you do not will except that Allāh wills - Lord of the worlds."
  83,19,"And what can make you know what is ʿilliyyūn?"
  83,20,"It is [their destination{1} recorded in] a register inscribed",footnotes:1:[The highest elevations of Paradise.]
  83,21,"Which is witnessed by those brought near [to Allāh]."
  84,16,"So I swear by the twilight glow"
  84,17,"And [by] the night and what it envelops"
  84,18,"And [by] the moon when it becomes full"
  85,13,"Indeed, it is He who originates [creation] and repeats."
  85,14,"And He is the Forgiving, the Affectionate,"
  85,15,"Honorable Owner of the Throne,"
  86,7,"Emerging from between the backbone and the ribs."
  86,8,"Indeed, He [i.e., Allāh], to return him [to life], is Able."
  86,9,"The Day when secrets will be put on trial,{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., exposed, examined and judged.]
  87,4,"And who brings out the pasture"
  87,5,"And [then] makes it black stubble."
  87,6,"We will make you recite, [O Muḥammad], and you will not forget,"
  88,1,"Has there reached you the report of the Overwhelming [event]?"
  88,2,"[Some] faces, that Day, will be humbled,"
  88,3,"Working [hard] and exhausted.{1}",footnotes:1:[Another accepted meaning is "They were working hard and exhausted," i.e., doing deeds during worldly life which did not benefit them since they were not accompanied by faith or done for the acceptance of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā) .]
